description.S:
Day-use passes are required before entering Garibaldi Park at Diamond Head, Rubble Creek, and Cheakamus.  As of September 5, passes are only required on weekends and holidays to visit Garibaldi Park.

Familiarizing yourself with the park through this in-depth trail walk-through will help you better prepare for your trip.  

Detailed program information and history can be found on the Day-Use Pass information page.

The road to Mount Seymour is provincially designated as a Winter Tire & Chain Route from Oct 1 to March 31. Mount Seymour staff reserve the right to enforce this requirement, ensuring vehicles have tires with the M+S symbol or, in extreme weather conditions, the peaked mount/snowflake symbol.

If your vehicle is not equipped with adequate tires and you still wish to access the park, the resort offers a shuttle service. If you are using the shuttle bus, you do not require a day-use pass.

The South Coast region covers Avalanche Canada’s Mount Seymour Park avalanche hazard rating. 

Before your trip, please check sunset times to ensure you depart with enough time to complete your intended hike.  

Understanding the importance of #LeaveNoTrace may help you better understand how to prepare for your trip.
